<DocsLayout title="Build" description="How the build phase works: direct Claude through tickets, verify each one, and ship.">
  <h1 class="mb-6">Build</h1>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">You've read the PRD, design spec, architecture, and backlog. Now you build. The build phase is where you direct Claude Code through every ticket in the backlog, one at a time, until the project is done.</p>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">Every ticket follows the same loop: <strong class="text-text">direct → verify → review → merge</strong>. You tell Claude to start a ticket. Claude implements it, commits, and opens a PR. You verify the result against the acceptance criteria. You read the reviews. You merge or ask for fixes. Then you move to the next ticket.</p>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-8">Work through these four sections in order:</p>

  <div class="grid gap-4">
    <Card title="1. Setup" subtitle="Create the project folder, open VS Code, launch Claude, and hand over the project files" href="/web-dev/projects/1/build/setup" />
    <Card title="2. Your first ticket" subtitle="A deep dive on the full ticket cycle: direct, verify, review, merge" href="/web-dev/projects/1/build/first-ticket" />
    <Card title="3. Remaining tickets" subtitle="Work through the rest of the backlog independently" href="/web-dev/projects/1/build/remaining-tickets" />
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
